   ('Why might a slope field be useful even before an exact solution to a differential equation has been found?', ['It provides a visual sense of how solutions generally behave across different regions of the plane', 'Slope fields provide no useful information about a differential equation’s behaviour', 'A differential equation must always be solved exactly before any visual representation is possible', 'This concept has no connection to understanding differential equations qualitatively'], 0),
