   ('Quark confinement describes the observation that individual quarks ___.', ['Are never found isolated in nature', 'Are commonly found existing completely independently', 'A concept unrelated to how quarks exist in nature', 'Do not actually exist as fundamental particles'], 0),
   ('Why does the strong force behave differently from gravity as the distance between particles increases?', ['The strong force actually increases in strength as quarks are pulled apart, unlike gravity, which weakens with distance', 'The strong force always weakens in exactly the same way as gravity does', 'Distance has no effect on the behaviour of the strong force', 'This concept has no connection to how fundamental forces operate'], 0),
   ('Which is an example of a composite particle made up of quarks bound together?', ['A proton', 'An electron, which is not made up of quarks', 'A particle entirely unrelated to the strong force', 'A photon, which carries no quark structure'], 0),
