   ('Why is zero electrical resistance in a superconductor considered a significant property?', ['It allows electric current to flow without any energy loss due to resistance, unlike ordinary conductors', 'Zero resistance has no meaningful benefit compared to typical conductors', 'Ordinary conductors already have zero electrical resistance under normal conditions', 'This property has no connection to how electric current flows through a material'], 0),
